==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Introspection
<hw>In`tro*spec"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>introspection</ets>.]</ety> <def>A view of the inside or interior;
a looking inward;</def> <specif>specifically,</specif> <def>the act or
process of self-examination, or inspection of one's own thoughts and
feelings; the cognition which the mind has of its own acts and states;
self-consciousness; reflection.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>I was forced to make an <qex>introspection</qex> into my own
mind.</q> <rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Introspectionist</ent>⟦br⟧
